title: For Sale:  Romanian PSL Dragunov
postcontent: Romanian PSL Dragunov sniper rifle built on a Nodak Spud receiver. The rifle wood has been refinished and looks Great! It's semi-automatic and it uses very powerful 7.62x54R caliber ammo. which is a Very Large round. Bigger than .308! The PSL is chambered for the same venerable 7.62x54mmR (rimmed) cartridge as the Dragunov, and feeds from a ten-round detachable box magazine. The magazine used on the PSL differs from that of Dragunov models in that it is stamped with an X shaped pattern on the side, rather than the waffle style stamp found on the Russian and Chinese magazines. The magazines, though they are similar in shape and size, are not interchangeable between the Dragunov and PSL without modification. The size of this round (7.62x54R) and the long barrel of the rifle allow shooting out to 1000yards plus. Comes with Two 10 round mags and a cleaning kit and sling. Also comes complete with scope that has a built in range finder reticle which was originally lit with radioactive Tritium. I can also ship to your local gun shop,if you are not local.
